In this code, we are using the StringTokenizer class to break the input string into tokens. We initialize a counter to keep track of the number of tokens we have processed. When we process the third token, we break the loop and return the token.

The parameter of the thirdToken method is the string that we want to break into tokens. This string is passed to the StringTokenizer constructor.

The method returns the third token of the string. If the string has less than 3 tokens, it returns an empty string.

